qbEthernetMIB.name: qbEthernetMIB
qbEthernetMIB.description: This module defines proprietary objects that extend those in IETF's the Ethernet-Like Interface MIB.

QbDot3LoopbackType.name: QbDot3LoopbackType
QbDot3LoopbackType.description: The type of loopback available on Quantum Bridge 802.3 (ethernet) interfaces.

qbDot3ConfigTable.name: qbDot3ConfigTable
qbDot3ConfigTable.description: Quantum Bridge proprietary configuration parameters for ethernet-like interfaces.

qbDot3ConfigEntry.name: qbDot3ConfigEntry
qbDot3ConfigEntry.description: Quantum Bridge proprietary configuration parameters for single ethernet-like interface.

qbDot3ConfigSpeed.name: qbDot3ConfigSpeed
qbDot3ConfigSpeed.description: The configured speed of the interface. This may be set by the administrator or may be the result of auto-negotiation.

qbDot3ConfigDuplexMode.name: qbDot3ConfigDuplexMode
qbDot3ConfigDuplexMode.description: The configured mode of the interface.

qbDot3ConfigEncapsType.name: qbDot3ConfigEncapsType
qbDot3ConfigEncapsType.description: The type of data encapsulation used over the AAL5 SSCS layer. The definitions reference RFC 1483 Multiprotocol Encapsulation over ATM AAL5 and to the ATM Forum LAN Emulation specification.

qbDot3ConfigRouterAddress.name: qbDot3ConfigRouterAddress
qbDot3ConfigRouterAddress.description: The MAC address of the router that connects to the IOT Ethnernet port. Note that this object is relevant for IOT ports only

qbDot3ConfigLoopback.name: qbDot3ConfigLoopback
qbDot3ConfigLoopback.description: The loopback configuration of this interface. If used in a set it will cause the agent to place the interface in the desired loopback mode. When read, it will return the interface's curretn loopback configuration.

qbDot3ConfigEnetAdminMode.name: qbDot3ConfigEnetAdminMode
qbDot3ConfigEnetAdminMode.description: This object identifies the default administrative baseband MAU type, to be used in conjunction with the operational MAU type denoted by ifMauType. For a detailed description see ifMauDefaultType in RFC2668.

qbDot3ConfigEnetType.name: qbDot3ConfigEnetType
qbDot3ConfigEnetType.description: This object identifies the MAU type. For a detailed description see ifMauType in RFC2668.

qbDot3ConfigEnetNegMode.name: qbDot3ConfigEnetNegMode
qbDot3ConfigEnetNegMode.description: This object is used to enable and disable auto-negotiation on a given port.

qbDot3Compliance.name: qbDot3Compliance
qbDot3Compliance.description: The compliance statement for all agents that support this MIB. A compliant agent implements all objects defined in this MIB.

qbDot3Group.name: qbDot3Group
qbDot3Group.description: The set of all accessible objects in this MIB.
